# Coding Rules for Mobile Applications

Use these rules when building or editing mobile apps. They apply to **React Native** (including Expo) and **Flutter**; framework-specific notes are called out where patterns differ.

---

## 1. Project structure

### React Native (and Expo)

- **Prefer feature-based organization** so everything for a feature lives together. Avoid scattering one feature across many top-level folders.
- **Recommended layout**:
  ```
  src/  (or app/ for Expo Router)
  ├── app/                    # [Expo Router] File-based routes: _layout.tsx, index.tsx, (tabs)/, [id].tsx
  ├── components/             # Reusable UI
  │   ├── common/             # Buttons, inputs, cards
  │   └── ui/                 # Design-system primitives
  ├── features/               # Feature modules (auth, profile, cart, …)
  │   └── <feature>/
  │       ├── components/     # Feature-specific components
  │       ├── screens/        # Screens used only in this feature
  │       ├── hooks/
  │       ├── store/ or state/
  │       └── types/
  ├── screens/                # Top-level screens if not using feature folders for all
  ├── navigation/            # Navigator config (when not using Expo Router)
  ├── services/              # API, auth, storage
  ├── store/                 # Global state (Redux, Zustand) if not per-feature
  ├── hooks/                  # App-wide hooks
  ├── utils/                  # Helpers
  ├── constants/              # Config, theme keys, API base URLs
  ├── types/                  # Shared TypeScript types
  ├── assets/                 # Images, fonts
  └── theme/                  # Colors, typography, spacing
  ```
- **Expo Router**: Put routes under `app/`. Use `_layout.tsx` for root layout and providers; `(groupName)/` for route groups; `[param].tsx` for dynamic segments. Keep navigation logic in layouts and links.
- **Convention**: One main entry (`App.tsx` or `app/_layout.tsx`). Config and env loaded at bootstrap.

### Flutter

- **Prefer feature-based + layered** under `lib/`:
  ```
  lib/
  ├── main.dart
  ├── app/                    # App bootstrap, routing, global providers
  ├── core/                   # App-wide: constants, theme, utils, extensions
  │   ├── constants/
  │   ├── theme/
  │   ├── utils/
  │   └── extensions/
  ├── shared/                 # Reusable widgets, services, models
  │   ├── widgets/
  │   └── services/
  ├── features/
  │   └── <feature>/
  │       ├── data/           # Repos, APIs, models, DTOs
  │       ├── domain/         # Entities, use cases
  │       └── presentation/   # Screens, widgets, state (BLoC/Cubit/Provider)
  └── l10n/                   # Generated localizations (if used)
  ```
- **Clean architecture**: Keep `data` (API, DB), `domain` (business rules), and `presentation` (UI + local state) clearly separated within each feature. Dependencies point inward (presentation → domain → data).
- **Barrel files**: Use `export` files (e.g. `widgets.dart`) to simplify imports; keep them thin.

### Cross-cutting

- **Assets**: Centralize under `assets/` (RN) or `assets/` with `pubspec.yaml` (Flutter). Use subfolders (e.g. `images/`, `fonts/`). Reference via constants or theme, not magic strings.
- **Config**: One place for API base URL, feature flags, and build config. Use env/build-time config; no hardcoded environment-specific values in source.

